<P>
Mickey Mouse wowed them on his debut on the London stock market Tuesday as 
investors scrambled for shares of the Euro Disneyland theme park. 
</P>
<P>
Shares in Euro Disneyland SCA opened in London at $13.12 (8.20 pounds 
sterling), compared to an issue price of $11.31 (7.07 sterling) fixed on Oct. 
5. 
</P>
<P>
Heavy demand for the stock before the formal flotation scheduled Nov. 3 had 
prompted the London Stock Exchange to take the unusual step of opening a 
limited, "advanced" market in unissued stock. 
</P>
<P>
Eurodisney plans a $1-billion stock offering in Paris and London, which will 
leave Walt Disney Co. with 49% of the company. 
</P>
